latestPosts.caption:
It’s that time of the year, the season of sparkle and vitality, and our grand festive issue is here to get you started! Our cover star is none other than the effervescent Tanisha Santoshi, who is ready to dazzle the Bollywood scene. Daughter of the renowned Indian film director, producer, and screenwriter, Rajkumar Santoshi, Tanisha’s infectious smile and killer looks will make your day. Flip through our Cover Story to get the lowdown on her life, her fitness game, upcoming projects, and all the juicy details!
Diwali, the Festival of Lights, is just around the corner, and we’re ready to dive headfirst into the five-day extravaganza, from Dhanteras to Bhai Dooj. Diwali, for most of us, is a wild mix of rangoli art, mouthwatering feasts, hanging out with the fam, and a time to celebrate the triumph of good over evil. It’s all about blessings, harmony, and that spark of enlightenment. In our Feature Story, we’ve got people from all over India and beyond sharing their special Diwali tales, what the festival means to them, and their epic plans for this year.
Do stop over at In The Spotlight, where we interview the extraordinary Khushboo Bagri, the creative genius behind the Khushboo Bagri Label. Her unique blend of Indian fashion with a modern twist celebrates craftsmanship and elegance. Dive into her creations for festive fashion inspiration.
In our “People in Focus,” we highlight two remarkable individuals. Meet Shabnam Gupta, the creative mind behind Peacock Life, who believes ‘design is for everyone.’ Her inclusive designs are showcased in her Hyderabad ventures, Peacock Life and Kosha. We also feature Aavika Chhawchharia, a culinary genius who turned her love for food into the beloved Honey & Dough confectionery and café in Delhi NCR. Explore their inspiring journeys.
If you have any suggestions, comments or queries, please e-mail me  at publisher@you-and-i.com.
